Can you move these down next to the other member variables? You can put an extra `public:` above them so that it's clear that these are public members.

~~~c++
public: 
    const UInt maxCapacity;
    const std::string ID; //name of this object
    const int DEBUG;
private:
    std::vector<T> buffer_;
    UInt idxNext_;
~~~

Here and elsewhere, you can reduce the nesting level a bit by using "get" with an appropriate default value, e.g.:

```
for input_field in app_spec.get('inputSpec', []):
    for suggestion in input_field.get('suggestions', []):
        if 'project' in suggestion:
```

I think `__eq__` should always return True or False.  At least I'm more comfortable that way.

